---
description: Git workflow safety for this repository
alwaysApply: true
---

- Do not commit directly to `main`.
- Do not push directly to `main`.
- For any meaningful code, test, or documentation change, work on a short-lived branch first.
- Before making changes, state the intended branch name.
- If currently on `main`, create and switch to a new branch before editing files.
- Prefer branch names like:
  - `feat/...`
  - `fix/...`
  - `test/...`
  - `docs/...`
  - `chore/...`
- After changes, recommend the smallest relevant test command first.
- Do not merge branches automatically unless explicitly asked.
- Do not delete branches automatically unless explicitly asked.